1
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:11,488
There's a weight of life
one can't bear on his own.

2
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,449
Hey, what's going on?

3
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,534
Get back or people will get hurt!

4
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,787
In order to disperse
the terminated employees

5
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:21,081
who were carrying out a strike
within the factory,

6
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:22,457
a SWAT team was mobilized.

7
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:24,501
The police commented that the operation

8
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:26,044
was well within the bounds of duty

9
00:01:26,127 --> 00:01:29,297
and that 20 or so union members
were arrested...

10
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:31,549
HUNGER STRIKE

11
00:01:35,845 --> 00:01:37,639
Let go!

12
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:42,519
DEMOLITION

13
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:55,990
But I must walk

14
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:59,077
with their weight on my shoulders.

15
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:02,747
Don't worry about the process.
Just look at the result.

16
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:05,583
If the process wasn't right,
the result won't be right either.

17
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,377
Do you have to win by all means?

18
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,629
Is that so important?
It's more important to win.

19
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,132
You said you wanted to change the world.

20
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:14,551
You must win to be able to do anything.

21
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:17,387
Tae-jun, but there is a line
you must never cross!

22
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,305
I do not care if you criticize my tactics.

23
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:21,808
You can't change anything without power.

24
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:23,726
I will do this.

25
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:25,645
And I will take responsibility.

26
00:02:38,283 --> 00:02:42,370
It is now time
for me to take responsibility.

27
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:59,804
EPISODE 10 WEIGHT OF 6 GRAMS

28
00:03:04,684 --> 00:03:08,396
These are the bank accounts
that we're assuming are Chairman Sung's.

29
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:11,149
Also, these are the log of deposits

30
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:13,109
made under his orders.

31
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:14,861
We must compare both materials

32
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:17,238
and find proof that links him to lobbying.

33
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:20,408
Most of the money was withdrawn
then handed out in person.

34
00:03:20,491 --> 00:03:22,285
It's the best way to leave no paper trail.

35
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:25,747
I'm sure that some of the money
was bounced around different accounts.

36
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:28,082
They could be labeled
as donations or operation expenses

37
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:30,168
to keep the trace clean.

38
00:03:30,251 --> 00:03:32,086
It might take a while,

39
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,589
but tracking the transaction
will get us to the truth.

40
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:36,049
Where shall we begin then?

41
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:37,759
Analyze the transactions.

42
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:39,677
Check the accounts

43
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:43,598
of the families and friends
of assemblymen, judges and prosecutors,

44
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:45,475
companies, and associations.

45
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:47,602
-Yes, ma'am.
-We're running out of time.

46
00:03:47,685 --> 00:03:49,395
Stop everything you're doing

47
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,189
and focus on tracking down the lobby.

48
00:03:51,272 --> 00:03:52,732
-Yes, sir.
-Got it, sir.

49
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:02,909
Tae-jun,

50
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,827
don't you need a rest?

51
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,038
-You don't look well.
-I'm fine.

52
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:12,669
Is there a way to get the accounts
of other banks just like Samyeong's?

53
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,170
I can look into it,

54
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,965
but I doubt it'll be easy.

55
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:24,764
Tae-jun, are you all right?

56
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:28,601
I just felt a little dizzy, that's all.

57
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:31,688
-You really should rest.
-There's no time for that.

58
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,898
I'll take care of this.

59
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,234
Let's get you home first.

60
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:49,622
Get some rest.

61
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,874
I'll call you
once we've looked at the files.

62
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,336
I'm sorry to leave
all the burden with you.

63
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,005
It's all right.

64
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,133
Tae-jun.

65
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:02,844
Don't try to carry
all the weight by yourself.

66
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,940
LIST OF BANK ACCOUNTS

67
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:24,449
Da-jeong, get this to Ms. Kang's office.

68
00:05:24,532 --> 00:05:25,992
Yes, sir.

69
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,995
Mr. Ahn wanted me to give you this.

70
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:30,496
-Good night then.
-You too.

71
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:34,417
It's from Mr. Jang's office.

72
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,211
These must be the accounts they checked.

73
00:05:39,172 --> 00:05:40,173
-Mr. Han.
-Yes?

74
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,761
Can you compare these accounts?

75
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:45,970
Yes, ma'am.

76
00:05:57,815 --> 00:05:59,817
Youngil Group's secretary's office
just called.

77
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:01,611
The files Jang Tae-jun acquired

78
00:06:02,987 --> 00:06:04,489
contain Chairman Sung's bank accounts

79
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:06,574
and the transactions made for lobbying.

80
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:09,744
Assemblyman Jang
and Assemblywoman Kang's offices

81
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:12,163
are searching for
the rightful owner of those accounts.

82
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:15,708
-Where's Chairman Sung?
-In the hospital, sir.

83
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:20,129
CHAIRMAN SUNG

84
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:22,256
He's been trying to contact you
since this morning.

85
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:24,050
I don't know what to do.

86
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,470
-I'll take it from here. You're dismissed.
-Yes, sir.

87
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:37,897
CHAIRMAN SUNG

88
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,152
We checked the transaction records
of the accounts

89
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:45,071
that we suspect are
made under borrowed-names.

90
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:49,325
Some were made
to members of the Daehan Party

91
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,369
and current and former
government employees.

92
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:54,872
The total amount we suspect
was lobbied is 19.3 billion won.

93
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:56,999
It's enough for an Independent Counsel.

94
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,335
Schedule a press conference.

95
00:06:59,418 --> 00:07:00,753
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

96
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,887
Why weren't you taking my calls?

97
00:07:11,305 --> 00:07:13,891
I was busy trying
to remedy the situation, sir.

98
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:16,894
They now have the list
of accounts and my ledger.

99
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:20,189
The world will now learn of
all the money I spread out there.

100
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,608
Do you have a way to stop this?

101
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,319
It's why I came to you in person.

102
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:33,202
Send out a press release after my speech.

103
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,162
Yes, ma'am.

104
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:35,746
Ma'am,

105
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:38,875
the prosecution is on the move.

106
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,629
Come in.

107
00:07:58,603 --> 00:08:03,399
Are you telling me to give up
everything I have?

108
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:10,823
I devoted my entire life
to get this far ahead.

109
00:08:11,407 --> 00:08:15,244
That money is what
bought you the seat you're in.

110
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,206
Mr. Sung, money isn't
what's at stake here.

111
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:21,209
Your money is what bought my seat,

112
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:25,087
but I wiped your behind
with my own bare hands.

113
00:08:25,546 --> 00:08:28,466
A fly can only take advantage
of a cow's back for so long.

114
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:31,844
Overstay its welcome,
and it'll get smacked by the tail.

115
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:40,978
So you'll save yourself
and leave me hanging?

116
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:44,524
I have to, in order to save you if I can.

117
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:47,527
This'll blow over in a few years.

118
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,947
Then, I'll issue a special pardon
for your release.

119
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,908
So for now, just do as I say.

120
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,876
Let's come clean about the lobbying

121
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,463
before they expose us first.

122
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,928
Minister Song Hui-seop

123
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:16,264
has invoked his investigative authority.

124
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:19,141
This morning, Minister Song

125
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:22,019
issued a command letter
regarding the investigation

126
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,230
into Youngil Group's slush fund.

127
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:26,691
He stated that he was taking over

128
00:09:26,774 --> 00:09:29,151
due to the fact that the prosecution

129
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:32,071
was dragging its feet
despite the public outrage.

130
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:34,031
The command letter is said to contain

131
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,950
the collection of evidence

132
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,660
regarding Youngil Group's lobbying

133
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:39,745
and the guideline into

134
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,956
Chairman Sung Yeong-gi's investigation.

135
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:45,376
The Minister of Justice
invoking his investigative authority

136
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:46,586
falls under the Act...

137
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,754
-Tae-jun.
-Yes, I'm watching.

138
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:51,841
Denying his right
will be an admission of guilt

139
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:55,344
which is why the prosecution
has no other option but to accept it.

140
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:56,804
I'm heading to the office.

141
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:59,974
The political circles commented
that the Minister of Justice

142
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,726
and the prosecutor general...

143
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:10,443
Even if we call for
an Independent Counsel,

144
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:12,069
we won't be able to get Song Hui-seop.

145
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,406
How many members in the office
received bribes from Chairman Sung?

146
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:17,908
We verified 12 counts.

147
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:22,038
Even if we reveal our findings,
they'll deny it

148
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:23,956
and paint it as a unilateral claim.

149
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,541
They'll still feel threatened though.

150
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,793
Not Minister Song,

151
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,587
but the current government.

152
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,088
You'll get the Blue House involved?

153
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,798
I hope they will work with us.

154
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,092
It might put you in danger.

155
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:38,346
Right.

156
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:41,932
But we can no longer
give Minister Song any more time.

157
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:49,523
Sir.

158
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,568
The Blue House just called.

159
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,737
The Chief Presidential Secretary
wants a word.

160
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,326
Come in.

161
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:05,956
Hello, sir.

162
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:07,917
I see you have company...

163
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:17,885
You won't believe
the traffic I faced on my way here.

164
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:22,014
Mr. Jang,

165
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:25,226
I'm curious as to what
brought you here to the Blue House.

166
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:28,896
Shouldn't you be resting
considering the injuries you received?

167
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,861
Sir, may I ask why you wanted to see me?

168
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:43,202
DONGBUK DAILY

169
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,664
The investigation
into Youngil Group's lobbies

170
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:48,541
is making its way to the Blue House.

171
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:50,835
Don't worry, sir.

172
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:54,004
It's why I invoked
my investigative authority

173
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,715
in order to swiftly
get to the bottom of this.

174
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,509
If Minister Song leads this investigation,

175
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:01,720
the public may see it
as the government's attempt of a cover-up.

176
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:03,389
You're still accused

177
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:05,558
of being involved
in the slush funds yourself.

178
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:06,559
So?

179
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,102
What are you suggesting?

180
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:11,480
You have to show that you are innocent
at the National Assembly.

181
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,941
Are you talking about a hearing?

182
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:17,486
If you're innocent,
it will do you more good than harm.

183
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:22,074
Sounds good to me.

184
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:26,120
But sir--

185
00:12:26,203 --> 00:12:28,956
I can't let the Blue House
be dragged into this.

186
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:32,001
Prove your innocence
regarding this scandal

187
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:35,171
and then focus on
the investigation afterwards.

188
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:38,757
Yes, of course.

189
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,562
Do you think you'll bring me down

190
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:54,398
with a special hearing?

191
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:03,866
The Judiciary Committee
will hold a special hearing.

192
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:05,576
Will it be as effective though?

193
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,953
The head of the Judiciary Committee

194
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:10,372
and assistant administrators
are Song's people.

195
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,875
His first course of action
will be to shut them up.

196
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:16,378
I know. That's why Song Hui-seop
accepted the hearing.

197
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:17,755
Then what's the plan?

198
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:22,092
Do you remember
how I helped him get his current seat?

199
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,850
-Will the trap work?
-We'll make it work.

200
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:33,437
It's our only chance
to bring Song Hui-seop down.

201
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:39,944
My hearing will be conducted soon,

202
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,947
so treating you to a meal is
the least I can do considering

203
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,114
how rough it'll get for you.

204
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:46,116
Let's eat then.

205
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,702
They say being well-fed even makes
ghosts look more handsome.

206
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:51,580
On which date shall we have the hearing?

207
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:54,041
-At the end of the month?
-Why wait?

208
00:13:54,124 --> 00:13:55,793
Let's strike while the iron is hot.

209
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:58,170
Make it happen as soon as possible.

210
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:00,339
Yes, sir.

211
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,841
No matter how hard
we try to have your back,

212
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,718
Jang Tae-jun will still come after you.

213
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:06,512
Look.

214
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,973
The head of the committee is here

215
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:11,517
and so are the administrators
of both parties.

216
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,018
There's only so much he can do.

217
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:17,773
Besides, I'll make sure
he doesn't attend the hearing.

218
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:23,529
I considered not ending his life
out of the goodness of my heart,

219
00:14:23,612 --> 00:14:26,323
but I have no choice
since he won't back down.

220
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:29,326
Anyway, let's eat
before the food goes cold.

221
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:30,911
Sure.

222
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,664
Keep this in mind before you eat though.

223
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:37,877
If this hearing hurts me in any way,

224
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,838
half of you will lose your jobs.

225
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:44,300
It's about time you earned your keep.

226
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:46,176
Don't you agree?

227
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:49,889
Let's eat.

228
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,406
How's the mood in the office?

229
00:15:07,489 --> 00:15:09,325
Minister Song taking over generated

230
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:10,993
some backlash among the prosecutors,

231
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:13,495
but none have been voicing their concerns.

232
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,956
He made a mockery out of us.

233
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,666
If you took the lead,

234
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,543
the prosecutors will have your back.

235
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:22,713
Do we have a suspect
on Jang Tae-jun's assault case?

236
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:24,632
A witness last spotted him
at Pyeongtaek Port.

237
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:26,842
He must be trying to leave the country.

238
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:30,095
The gang he used to belong to
should have a smuggler.

239
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:31,972
-Contact him to track him down.
-Yes, sir.

240
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:34,308
Sir,

241
00:15:35,225 --> 00:15:37,937
should we still be helping
Jang Tae-jun though?

242
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:41,774
The Supreme Prosecutors' Office
will investigate him.

243
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,026
On what charges?

244
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,528
Illegal utilization of
the police's internal documents

245
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:49,156
and the cover-up
of Assemblyman Jo's bribery.

246
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:56,080
Just carry on. What we're doing
isn't to help Jang Tae-jun.

247
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:57,915
We're trying to bring Song Hui-seop down

248
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,709
and upright the discipline
of the prosecutors' office.

249
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:01,710
Yes, sir.

250
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:03,671
I'll be in touch.

251
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,640
ASSEMBLYMAN JANG TAE-JUN

252
00:16:18,686 --> 00:16:21,230
We must shake Minister Song up
before the hearing.

253
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:24,566
I sent out a press release
which state that he and Chairman Sung

254
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:26,360
was at the scene of your assault,

255
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:28,112
but no one's willing to publish the story.

256
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,073
The same goes for Dodam Daily.

257
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:33,993
And...

258
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:37,496
The hearing has been scheduled.

259
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,000
He won't give us time to get ready.

260
00:16:41,542 --> 00:16:42,793
Will Chairman Sung testify?

261
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:45,337
He's refusing to take the stand
due to health issues.

262
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:47,006
His heart surgery

263
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:48,841
has been booked on that day.

264
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:52,344
A doctor already signed off on it,
so it'll be hard to force him there.

265
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:54,179
Ask for all the material

266
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:56,306
regarding Minister Song and Chairman Sung

267
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,976
including documents
from Minister Song's confirmation hearing.

268
00:16:59,059 --> 00:17:01,937
We must find the link
between the two of them.

269
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:03,397
Yes, sir.

270
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,191
Sir.

271
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:10,529
I'll help Assemblyman Jang
prepare for the hearing.

272
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:13,782
Gather all the material
you have on Minister Song.

273
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:16,201
We don't have enough time to prepare.

274
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:17,911
Would the hearing even be effective?

275
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:19,455
We only need to find one thing.

276
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:21,457
The link between
Minister Song and Chairman Sung.

277
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:25,044
Anyway, get me ready for the meeting.

278
00:17:25,627 --> 00:17:26,879
Yes, ma'am.

279
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:29,214
Ma'am.

280
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,427
The prosecution has begun
its investigation

281
00:17:33,510 --> 00:17:35,137
into Assemblyman Jang Tae-jun.

282
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:38,057
Earlier, the prosecution revealed

283
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:41,560
that Mr. Jang leaked internal information
within the police force.

284
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:44,021
The prosecution will soon summon Mr. Jang

285
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,482
and begin an investigation on
how he obtained such materials,

286
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:48,525
his knowledge of illegality
concerning his actions,

287
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:49,943
and his motives for the crime

288
00:17:50,027 --> 00:17:52,696
as well as planning and repetition
of such illegal activity.

289
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:55,240
If he is found guilty of

290
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:58,285
deliberately leaking the information
he obtained to a third party,

291
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:00,704
he could be arrested for further...

292
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:06,126
The prosecution issued a warrant out
for your arrest.

293
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:09,129
A summons will be issued soon.

294
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,799
I think he means to stop you
from attending the hearing.

295
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:13,967
You can refuse to be questioned
with your immunity.

296
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,719
It may not side well with the public,

297
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,387
but it's your only option.

298
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,556
It's what Minister Song wants.

299
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:21,975
If they find you

300
00:18:22,059 --> 00:18:24,269
incompetent to lead the hearing--

301
00:18:24,353 --> 00:18:26,563
It will be forced to stop.

302
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:29,650
We can change the target.

303
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:33,362
Let the prosecution

304
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:35,155
question me instead.

305
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:37,783
I knew the documents
were obtained illegally.

306
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:41,411
You tried to stop me,
but I disobeyed your orders.

307
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:47,751
Send out a press release saying
that I acted on my own accord.

308
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:50,629
-Sure.
-Hye-won,

309
00:18:51,213 --> 00:18:53,257
assemblymen may have immunity,
but you don't.

310
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:55,801
You could be arrested
right after being questioned.

311
00:18:55,884 --> 00:18:57,261
Must you go this far?

312
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:00,889
I'm his chief of staff.

313
00:19:02,057 --> 00:19:04,309
It's my job to protect him
until the very end.

314
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:06,812
Ms. Yun...

315
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:09,690
Please do a good job
preparing for the hearing.

316
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:16,613
Going down.

317
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:25,747
I'll turn myself in.

318
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:27,166
Let me do it.

319
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:28,167
Hye-won,

320
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:31,044
this is my burden to bear.

321
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:33,297
But you also have a job to do.

322
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,048
Only think about that right now.

323
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:36,967
We can't let Minister Song

324
00:19:38,135 --> 00:19:39,303
get his way.

325
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:42,014
Do not let this be the end.

326
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:55,777
ASSEMBLYMAN JANG TAE-JUN

327
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:01,575
Jang Tae-jun's office
sent out a press release.

328
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:03,911
They're claiming that
Yun Hye-won acted on her own

329
00:20:03,994 --> 00:20:05,746
without Jang Tae-jun's approval.

330
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:07,414
Where is she right now?

331
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:10,042
She has already come by to be questioned.

332
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:13,879
At this moment, it'll be difficult
to have Jang Tae-jun arrested too.

333
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,216
They're trying to buy some time.

334
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:20,594
Come in.

335
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:30,771
Sir, here are the lists of requests
from Assemblyman Jang's office.

336
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:33,148
Let me see.

337
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:35,817
REQUESTED MATERIAL
HEARING FOR YOUNGIL GROUP SLUSH FUND CASE

338
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:37,361
Goodness.

339
00:20:37,986 --> 00:20:39,905
Goodness me. What a long list.

340
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:42,532
I guess I should show some action.

341
00:20:44,409 --> 00:20:46,954
Gather some documents and send them over.

342
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:47,996
Yes, sir.

343
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:52,084
Also, I've blocked all media outlets
from reporting about you.

344
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:53,085
Good.

345
00:20:54,127 --> 00:20:57,422
I made sure that
the reporters at the conference

346
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,132
kept their mouth shut,

347
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:00,884
so how did

348
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:04,972
Yun Hye-won know that
I was with Chairman Sung?

349
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:19,695
Gwi-dong...

350
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:24,825
Nothing.

351
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,469
These are from the Ministry of Justice.

352
00:21:44,636 --> 00:21:45,929
They sent over plenty but...

353
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:49,558
The files we requested aren't here
and trash is all they sent over.

354
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:51,935
Are we supposed to recycle these?

355
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,646
-What about the prosecution?
-We received files via email,

356
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:57,149
but key words and phrases
have been redacted.

357
00:21:57,232 --> 00:22:01,153
Will any of these lead to the connection
between Minister Song and Chairman Sung?

358
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,946
It's like finding a needle in a haystack.

359
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:05,073
Forget about the materials they sent us.

360
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:07,200
They're probably a bust anyway.

361
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:08,952
Why don't we focus on

362
00:22:09,036 --> 00:22:11,204
the bills proposed by Minister Song?

363
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,081
He could've proposed those that benefited

364
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:14,750
Youngil Group's subsidiaries

365
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,210
or covered up any investigation into them.

366
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:20,589
The files within the National Assembly
could give us a fighting chance.

367
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:22,799
Financial investments
is Youngil Group's main business.

368
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:25,844
During the 17th assembly election,
Song was on the National Policy Committee.

369
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:28,305
Look into the bills proposed then
and committee minutes.

370
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,059
-Mr. Ahn.
-Right.

371
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:34,478
-Mr. Park.
-Thanks.

372
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:35,562
Here you go, sir.

373
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:39,441
-Can you check these?
-Sure.

374
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:40,525
Ma'am.

375
00:22:41,443 --> 00:22:45,030
As you can see, the bills were
about FTA with Vietnam and others...

376
00:22:48,408 --> 00:22:50,869
Here are the bills
proposed by Minister Song at the time.

377
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:53,371
-They're in chronological order.
-Thank you.

378
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:58,251
Minister Song tabled multiple bills

379
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:00,754
that benefited Youngil Group's interest.

380
00:23:00,837 --> 00:23:03,298
However, most were joint motions.

381
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:07,094
Ahn Hyeon-min and No Seung-jin
proposed the bills with him.

382
00:23:07,385 --> 00:23:09,429
That's not enough
to tie those two together.

383
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:12,224
Even before he became a prosecutor,
Minister Song

384
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:14,518
was close to Chairman Sung.

385
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:17,270
Is there a way to prove that?

386
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:22,150
There is.

387
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:25,737
Someone who is always
by Minister Song's side.

388
00:23:32,452 --> 00:23:34,621
I hear your daughter is getting married.

389
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:36,331
Yes, sir.

390
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:39,459
The wedding takes place this month.

391
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:40,836
Has she purchased a house yet?

392
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:43,004
Not yet, sir.

393
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:44,840
Buying one in Seoul isn't easy.

394
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,426
Find something appropriate

395
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,804
and I'll buy it for her.

396
00:23:51,304 --> 00:23:53,682
-Sorry?
-You've been my driver for 20 years.

397
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:56,143
It'll be my pleasure.

398
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,228
Don't think too much about it
and find a place.

399
00:23:58,311 --> 00:24:00,856
Consider it a wedding gift.

400
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:04,025
Yes, sir.

401
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:25,338
-Good night, sir.
-You too.

402
00:24:37,517 --> 00:24:38,560
ASSEMBLYMAN JANG TAE-JUN

403
00:24:38,643 --> 00:24:41,062
Gwi-dong, can we meet?

404
00:24:44,649 --> 00:24:46,151
How are your injuries?

405
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:48,195
Should you even be out and about?

406
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:50,363
I'm better now.

407
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:52,616
Ms. Yun told me.

408
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:56,494
You told her about Minister Song.

409
00:24:56,578 --> 00:25:00,874
Oh, that. I doubt it was any help,
but I hoped it could be.

410
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:04,377
I was wondering
if you could help us once again.

411
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:07,172
We're looking for bearer bonds

412
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:09,799
that Chairman Sung gave to Minister Song.

413
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:13,970
I thought you'd have an idea
as to where they'd be.

414
00:25:14,930 --> 00:25:16,473
I want to help you,

415
00:25:16,556 --> 00:25:20,894
but he's not the type of person
who'd let me see him do such business.

416
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:22,229
Then I'll look for them myself.

417
00:25:23,521 --> 00:25:25,732
Could you please let me

418
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:27,943
look at your driving log?

419
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:29,861
My driving log?

420
00:25:34,824 --> 00:25:38,745
These show where Minister Song went
and whom he met over the past 20 years.

421
00:25:38,828 --> 00:25:40,789
Crosscheck the entry logs

422
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:43,667
with when Minister Song met Chairman Sung.

423
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:44,834
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

424
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:58,390
The hearing regarding
the Youngil Group slush fund

425
00:25:58,473 --> 00:26:00,267
will begin soon at 10 a.m.

426
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:02,185
Today, Minister Song,

427
00:26:02,269 --> 00:26:04,688
who is said to be directly involved,

428
00:26:04,771 --> 00:26:07,857
will attend the hearing
as the witness himself

429
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:09,734
to explain his intentions

430
00:26:09,818 --> 00:26:12,654
as to why he invoked
his investigative authority.

431
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:16,116
-Go easy on me today.
-Sure.

432
00:26:16,199 --> 00:26:17,784
-Good day.
-Hello, sir.

433
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:19,619
Good luck, sir.

434
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:29,254
I'm excited to see what you prepared
at the expense of your chief of staff.

435
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,049
Good luck.

436
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,854
We must have it
before the hearing is over.

437
00:26:46,938 --> 00:26:48,273
I'll try my best.

438
00:26:55,488 --> 00:26:56,573
Yes, Chief Choe.

439
00:26:57,699 --> 00:26:58,742
It's Kang Seon-yeong.

440
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:06,082
Let us begin the hearing.

441
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:10,837
"I, Song Hui-seop,

442
00:27:11,254 --> 00:27:14,257
swear to only tell the truth
and nothing but the truth

443
00:27:14,341 --> 00:27:16,426
regarding the slush fund of Youngil Group

444
00:27:16,509 --> 00:27:19,387
according to Article Seven

445
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:22,682
of the Act on Testimony, Appraisal, Etc.

446
00:27:22,766 --> 00:27:26,936
with good conscience and without deceit
before the National Assembly.

447
00:27:27,437 --> 00:27:31,775
I understand that lying today
will be considered as perjury

448
00:27:31,858 --> 00:27:34,235
which is punishable by law."

449
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:37,947
Minister Song won't ever

450
00:27:38,656 --> 00:27:40,075
take that risk.

451
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:41,618
He will once we corner him.

452
00:27:42,869 --> 00:27:46,122
What we're looking for
will be the smoking gun.

453
00:27:46,956 --> 00:27:50,043
We need your help
to arrest Minister Song for good.

454
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:56,007
It could work if everything goes
as Mr. Jang plans.

455
00:27:56,508 --> 00:27:57,634
But if it goes wrong,

456
00:27:57,717 --> 00:28:02,889
not only him but the two of us
will also become criminals.

457
00:28:03,473 --> 00:28:06,059
That is a risk both you, Chief, and I

458
00:28:06,976 --> 00:28:08,061
must take.

459
00:28:11,898 --> 00:28:13,775
As the Minister of Justice,

460
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:16,444
you invoked your investigative authority

461
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:18,738
to secure a thorough investigation
of this case.

462
00:28:18,822 --> 00:28:22,117
Don't you think you ruffled some feathers
with the prosecution?

463
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:24,828
It's true that I was met
with some backlash,

464
00:28:25,245 --> 00:28:28,123
but I only acted in a way
which seemed just.

465
00:28:28,206 --> 00:28:30,583
Yes, I agree.

466
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:32,585
Thanks to your brave decision,

467
00:28:32,669 --> 00:28:34,754
I believe we were able to

468
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:37,841
promptly arrest
and question Chairman Sung Yeong-gi.

469
00:28:38,341 --> 00:28:39,384
Thank you.

470
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:42,137
It's like they're giving him
a medal of honor

471
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,596
instead of questioning him.

472
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:47,100
At this rate, what Mr. Jang says
won't even stir up a response.

473
00:28:48,184 --> 00:28:51,354
Still, I believe that
he'll make something happen.

474
00:28:54,441 --> 00:28:56,234
Mr. Jang, ask your question.

475
00:28:58,528 --> 00:29:00,447
I am Jang Tae-jun of the Daehan Party.

476
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,282
JANG TAE-JUN

477
00:29:02,365 --> 00:29:04,409
During your time as a prosecutor,
you were assigned

478
00:29:04,492 --> 00:29:07,328
to a case regarding
Youngil Group's slush fund.

479
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:10,248
I'm sure you have
a close relationship with Chairman Sung.

480
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:12,208
Yes, we're acquaintances.

481
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:14,461
You two are more than mere acquaintances.

482
00:29:14,544 --> 00:29:17,589
Right after investigating that case,
you resigned as a prosecutor,

483
00:29:17,672 --> 00:29:19,299
and ran in the general election.

484
00:29:19,382 --> 00:29:21,801
Wasn't it because of Chairman Sung?

485
00:29:23,094 --> 00:29:25,388
One doesn't make
such an important decision

486
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:27,891
based on someone else's suggestion.

487
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:31,436
It was my decision to become a politician.

488
00:29:31,519 --> 00:29:33,855
Once the revised bill
of the Tourism Promotion Act was passed

489
00:29:34,022 --> 00:29:36,775
after you proposed it, a hotel of
one of Youngil Group's subsidiaries

490
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:39,569
was built near a historic site.
The bill allowing business reshuffle

491
00:29:39,652 --> 00:29:41,654
led to Youngil Group acquire
its rival company.

492
00:29:41,738 --> 00:29:44,115
That and many other bills you proposed

493
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:46,826
were to benefit
Youngil Group's operations.

494
00:29:46,910 --> 00:29:50,079
Don't tell me you're still claiming
that you have no ties to Chairman Sung.

495
00:29:50,872 --> 00:29:53,583
I say this on behalf
of my status as minister.

496
00:29:53,666 --> 00:29:57,712
In no way have I ever
proposed a bill to benefit Youngil Group.

497
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:04,177
This is your secretary's notepad

498
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:07,931
which contains where you've been
and who you've met

499
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:10,183
for the past 20 years.

500
00:30:12,227 --> 00:30:13,603
-What?
-Hold on.

501
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:15,230
Out of all the entries here,

502
00:30:15,313 --> 00:30:18,942
we looked into the places you visited
which weren't for official business.

503
00:30:19,025 --> 00:30:21,694
Restaurants, bars, golf clubs,
hotels, saunas and many more.

504
00:30:21,778 --> 00:30:24,197
Here are when you visited those places.

505
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:27,492
Also, we looked into whether or not
Chairman Sung was there

506
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:30,411
or at least had a reservation
on those dates.

507
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:34,290
It turns out that
when you visited those places,

508
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:36,125
Chairman Sung also came by

509
00:30:36,209 --> 00:30:38,169
on 84 occasions this year.

510
00:30:38,253 --> 00:30:41,589
For the past few decades,
you and Chairman Sung

511
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:44,717
also flew abroad on the same date
on 72 occasions.

512
00:30:44,801 --> 00:30:46,803
Even when all this evidence exists,

513
00:30:46,886 --> 00:30:50,557
